The paper discusses a technique for reducing the Peak to Average Power Ratio (PAPR) in Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing (OFDM) systems. This topic falls under the field of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a new technique for signal detection and optimization, which could fall under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Space Time Bloc Codes (STBC) and precoding sequences, which could fall under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed methods using the Max-Log-Maximum A Posteriori (MAP) algorithm, which could fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
